# Star field / galaxy shaders — dark-pixel replacement
## These shaders check pixel brightness and only apply to pixels below a threshold (~0.1).
## Clever: keeps text readable by only replacing dark background areas.
## Result: works in dark-themed apps (NeoVim dark), invisible in light themes/shell, or in themes that are not quite dark enough.
# Star field animation
# Review: trippy! Pretty nice in neovim. But probably would never _actually_ it.
# custom-shader = ../shaders/community/starfield.glsl
# Colorful star field — same as above but with colored stars
# custom-shader = ../shaders/community/starfield-colors.glsl
# Galaxy background
# custom-shader = ../shaders/community/galaxy.glsl

# Fireworks particles
# Review: works but looks cheap
# custom-shader = ../shaders/community/fireworks.glsl

# Fireworks with rockets
# Review: even worse than fireworks
